The hermit crab fauna of submarine caves in the Ryukyu Islands, southwestern Japan , has been studied in recent years, with 30 species, including some new species described from there (cf.
;
,
). During ongoing surveys of the fauna and topography of submarine caves in the Ryukyu Islands led by the second author (cf.
), the first and second authors recently collected an unusual hermit crab from the anchialine environment of a semi-submerged marine cave on the western-central coast of Okinawa Island, central Ryukyus. The present paper describes it as a new species and the fifth member of the genus
Trichopagurus
.

